As part of debugging a shell file registered as a concurrent program which was not seeming to find the correct java executable, I needed to find out the values of the environment variables values at time of execution without having access to the server or being able to modify the code.<br />
<br />
Can't remember which note exactly, but on Metalink I found about table fnd_env_context and a query to retrieve the variables and its values. This is quite helpful for debugging.<br />
<br />
